<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Another night of Nations League action is upon us as Italy, Holland, Northern Ireland and Scotland all begin their campaign tonight. </p>

<p>The Italians kick off their tournament against Bosnia and Herzegovina as Roberto Mancini hopes his side can get off to a fast start on home soil. </p>

<p>The other match from Group 1 in League A will see Virgil van Dijk and his Holland team-mates host Poland after the recent departure of head coach Ronald Koeman, who left for Barcelona.  </p>

<p>Elsewhere, two home nations are beginning their new Nations League ventures as Northern Ireland travel to Romania in Group 1 of League B, whilst over in Group 2, Scotland welcome Israel as Steve Clarke hopes to begin in winning ways with ties against Czech Republic and Slovakia to come.</p>

<p>Here, Sportsmail's IEUAN IVETT will provide all the updates as another night of Nations League action unfolds.</p>
